Rename Interface Using Udev Rules (Recommended)
Find Interface Details
Run:

bash
Copy
Edit
udevadm info /sys/class/net/ens225 | grep -E 'ID_NET_NAME|ID_PATH|ID_NET_NAME_MAC'
Example output:

ini
Copy
Edit
ID_NET_NAME_MAC=xx:xx:xx:xx:xx:xx
ID_PATH=pci-0000:03:00.0
Create a Udev Rule to Rename Interface
Create a custom udev rule:

bash
Copy
Edit
sudo nano /etc/udev/rules.d/70-persistent-net.rules
Add the following line (replace MAC or PCI path with actual values):

ini
Copy
Edit
SUBSYSTEM=="net", ACTION=="add", ATTR{address}=="xx:xx:xx:xx:xx:xx", NAME="ens256"
OR (if using PCI path)

ini
Copy
Edit
SUBSYSTEM=="net", ACTION=="add", ATTR{devpath}=="pci-0000:03:00.0", NAME="ens256"
Apply Changes and Reboot

bash
Copy
Edit
sudo udevadm control --reload-rules
sudo udevadm trigger
sudo reboot
After reboot, check:

bash
Copy
Edit
ip a
